RAILO-2770</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Railo added the possibility to set the request timeout in the Application.cfc</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">(also this.timeout is supported as alias, for compatibility to ACF)</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Exampe:</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 9px 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; font-family: monospace; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; background: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<pre style=\"padding: 0px; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow: auto; font-size: 1em; clear: both; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: \'andale mono\', \'lucida console\', monospace; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 30em; word-wrap: normal; background: transparent;\">\r\n<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 145); background: transparent;\">this</span><font color=\"#333333\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">.requestTimeout=<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />createTimespan(0,0,0,20)</font><font color=\"#333333\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">;</font><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background: transparent;\"> </span></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">GZip Compression</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2784\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2784</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\">Railo added support for enable/disable gzip compression in Application.cfc</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\">Example:</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 9px 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; font-family: monospace; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; background: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<pre style=\"padding: 0px; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow: auto; font-size: 1em; clear: both; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: \'andale mono\', \'lucida console\', monospace; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 30em; word-wrap: normal; background: transparent;\">\r\n<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 145); background: transparent;\">this</span><font color=\"#333333\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">.compress=</font><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 145); line-height: 1.33333333333333; background: transparent;\">true</span><font color=\"#333333\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; background: transparent;\">;</font><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background: transparent;\"> </span>\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Logging</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2728\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2728</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Railo 4.2 has a completely rewritten logging framework which is now using log4j instead of a custom one previously. In addition, in the Railo admin you now can inspect all logs created by Railo and you can control where log files are written and how the output looks like. Railo 4.2 dramatically improves performance for the existing logging</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Log &quot;cfcatch&quot;</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2727\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2727</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Railo added a new attribute &quot;exception&quot; to the tag &lt;cflog&gt;, to make it possible to send exceptions (cfcatch) directly to a log.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Example:\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 9px 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; font-family: monospace; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<pre style=\"padding: 0px; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow: auto; font-size: 1em; clear: both; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: \'andale mono\', \'lucida console\', monospace; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 30em; word-wrap: normal; background: transparent;\">\r\n&lt;cftry&gt;\r\n	&lt;cfthrow message=<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;shit happens!!!&quot;</span>&gt;\r\n	&lt;cfcatch&gt;\r\n		&lt;cflog application=<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;true&quot;</span> type=<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;error&quot;</span> exception=<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;#cfcatch#&quot;</span>&gt;\r\n	&lt;/cfcatch&gt;\r\n&lt;/cftry&gt;</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Administrator Frontend</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2794\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2794</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2829\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2829</a></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">There is now a page in the Railo Administrator to manage all the log files used</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Attribute &quot;log&quot; improved</b><br style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />\r\n<a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2802\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2802</a><br style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />\r\nSince you now can define several individual loggers in the Railo&nbsp;Administrator, by giving them a name, you can use every of these loggers defined in the extended attribute &quot;log&quot;. So you can not only use&nbsp;&quot;scheduler&quot; and &quot;application&quot; but you can define your custom logger in the Administrator and use it within the attribute. This is similar to the way you use a datasource name.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Example:</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 9px 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; font-family: monospace; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background: rgb(245, 245, 245);\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<pre style=\"padding: 0px; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow: auto; font-size: 1em; clear: both; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-family: \'andale mono\', \'lucida console\', monospace; line-height: 1.5; max-height: 30em; word-wrap: normal; background: transparent;\">\r\n&lt;cflog&nbsp;<span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; background: transparent;\"> log=</span><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;myCustomLogger&quot;</span><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; background: transparent;\"> message=</span><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; color: rgb(0, 145, 0); background: transparent;\">&quot;#msg#&quot;</span><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.33333333333333; background: transparent;\">&gt;</span></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Exceptions</b></span></font></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\">Railo 4.2 improves the information you receive when an exception is raised. For example when you use a non-existing key in your code, Railo checks if there is a similar key available and informs about this key in the error message.</span></font></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Lock increase Exception message</b></span></font></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2730\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2730</a></span></font></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><font color=\"#333333\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20px; background: transparent;\">When a lock severity is getting increased inside an inner lock from read to exclusive, an exception thrown indicating that it was not possible to acquire the lock. In this particular case it is helpful to know why the error occurred. So the exception is informing you that your request already performed read lock and you now try to acquire an exclusive lock.</span></font></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><b style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">ORM Exceptions</b></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://issues.jboss.org/browse/RAILO-2531\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" target=\"_blank\">https://issues.jboss.org/<wbr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" />browse/RAILO-2531</a></div>\r\nImproved ORM Exceptions</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n',0,'2014-08-11 10:06:33','2014-08-11 10:06:33',NULL,1,NULL,'Some of you maybe already saw that we releases yesterday Railo 4.2 final (was about time!).\nWe did this as part of our \"Railo 4.2/5.0\" presentation at cf.objective as a soft release.\nSo ATM you can update in the Railo Admin, but there are no downloads available on our website yet,\nbut this will follow soon. ...'),(8,'Railo Server and the Heartbleed vulnerability','<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Recently there has been a lot of buzz around one of the largest vulnerabilities in SSL, the<a href=\"http://www.heartbleed.com/\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Heartbeat</a>&nbsp;exploit. There have been questions from the CFML community whether or how Railo Server is affected by this security threat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Railo Server is a servlet that runs on any servlet engine and therefore by itself (except perhaps for the libraries it uses) not potentially affected by the Heartbleed vulnerability.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"padding: 0px 0px 1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1; font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; color: rgb(60, 62, 64); border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: -0.01em; background-image: url(http://blog.getrailo.com/skins/railo/assets/images/hr_title_sep.gif); background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 100%; background-repeat: no-repeat;\">Railo Server internal libraries</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">What libraries which deal with SSL does Railo internally use?</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em 40px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Railo uses several libraries that are dealing with SSL. Amongst them there is one that makes use of OpenSSL. Some details.\r\n	<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 30px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 1em !important; background: transparent;\">\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">This library is called bcprov-jdk14.jar which is already several years old and therefore alone by this fact not affected by the Heartbleed bug.</li>\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Next to that the library implements only the SSL client which is anyway not affected by the bug, even though there are issues on the client side as well (see links below).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">All other libraries Railo uses, use a different SSL library. In any event, these libraries provide an SSL client which anyway is not affected by the bug.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Here are all libraries in the current Railo distributions that use some form of SSL:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; width: 339px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\" width=\"339\">\r\n	<tbody style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\"><strong style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; font-size: 1em !important; background: transparent;\">Library name</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-commons-httpclient.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-commons-sanselan.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-jakarta-commons-fileupload.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-jakarta-commons-httpclient.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-jakarta-commons-net.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-poi-ooxml-schemas.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">apache-poi.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">bcprov-jdk14.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">flex-messaging-proxy.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">h2.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">javaparser.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">jencrypt.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">jfreechart.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">jpedal_gpl.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">jtds.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">microsoft-sqljdbc.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">ojdbc14.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">PDFRenderer.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">postgresql.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">sun-jai_core.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">sun-mail.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">\r\n			<td style=\"padding: 0.5em; margin: 0px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); outline: 0px; vertical-align: top; line-height: 1.2; background: transparent;\">xdb.jar</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"padding: 0px 0px 1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.25em; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1; font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; color: rgb(60, 62, 64); border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; letter-spacing: -0.01em; background-image: url(http://blog.getrailo.com/skins/railo/assets/images/hr_title_sep.gif); background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0px 100%; background-repeat: no-repeat;\">Servlet containers</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em 40px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Tomcat:\r\n	<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 30px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 1em !important; background: transparent;\">\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Our research revealed that the &quot;tcnative&quot; library is the only piece of Tomcat that is potentially affected as it is the only piece of Tomcat that uses an OpenSSL implementation of SSL.</li>\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Java&#39;s implementation of SSL (JSSE) is not vulnerable. The Railo Tomcat installers don&rsquo;t do anything with tcnative since most users will use Apache, nginx or IIS to serve up SSL</li>\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Unless you have specifically compiled tcnative for your system, your instances are safe from a Railo/Tomcat point of view.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Jetty\r\n	<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 30px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; font-size: 1em !important; background: transparent;\">\r\n		<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Jetty uses JSSE as well, so it&#39;s not effected either.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">So from a Railo perspective you are safe, if you use our official downloads for your system installation. If however you have built your own system ontop of Tomcat and Apache, nginx&nbsp;etc, you need to follow the different procedures in order to protect your system. There are several different tools out there in order to test and update your systems. The main heartbleed site contains a list of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Links:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em 40px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://heartbleed.com/\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://heartbleed.com/</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55249/what-clients-are-proven-to-be-vulnerable-to-heartbleed\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55249/what-clients-are-proven-to-be-vulnerable-to-heartbleed</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55249/what-clients-are-proven-to-be-vulnerable-to-heartbleed\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55249/what-clients-are-proven-to-be-vulnerable-to-heartbleed</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://beta.slashdot.org/story/200551\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://beta.slashdot.org/story/200551</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55180/does-heartbleed-vulnerability-affect-other-libraries-like-bouncycastle-nets\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://security.stackexchange.com/questions/55180/does-heartbleed-vulnerability-affect-other-libraries-like-bouncycastle-nets</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"https://wiki.apache.org/tomcat/Security/Heartbleed\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">https://wiki.apache.org/tomcat/Security/Heartbleed</a></li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><a href=\"http://securityintelligence.com/heartbleed-openssl-vulnerability-what-to-do-protect/\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 1em !important; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://securityintelligence.com/heartbleed-openssl-vulnerability-what-to-do-protect/</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',0,'2014-08-11 10:08:06','2014-08-11 10:08:06',NULL,1,NULL,'Recently there has been a lot of buzz around one of the largest vulnerabilities in SSL, theHeartbeat exploit. There have been questions from the CFML community whether or how Railo Server is affected by this security threat. ...'),(9,'Railo Server software archive now online','<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">But what if you need to install version 3.2.2.000, or 3.1.2.001, because that&#39;s what your client runs on? Or perhaps you&#39;d like to test&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/gert_railo/status/145301270830383106\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">how much faster</a>&nbsp;Railo Server became between version 1.0 and 3.3?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Well today, we are happy to announce the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.getrailo.org/index.cfm/download/olderversions/\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Railo Server archive</a>, where you can find versions of Railo Server going all the way back to Railo 1.0! The archive is not yet complete, but almost all main versions and all release candidates for 3.3 are now online and downloadable!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">Check it out at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.getrailo.org/index.cfm/download/olderversions/\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">http://www.getrailo.org/index.cfm/download/olderversions/</a></p>\r\n',0,'2014-08-11 10:12:42','2014-08-11 10:12:42',NULL,1,NULL,'But what if you need to install version 3.2.2.000, or 3.1.2.001, because that\'s what your client runs on? Or perhaps you\'d like to test how much faster Railo Server became between version 1.0 and 3.3? ...'),(10,'Railo for Beginners: The Book!','<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\"><a href=\"http://www.packtpub.com/railo-3-beginners-guide-to-develop-deploy-complex-applications-online/book\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" title=\"Railo 3 Beginner‚Äôs Guide: RAW Book &amp; eBook | Packt Publishing Technical &amp; IT Book and eBook Store\">Railo for Beginners</a>, written by Mark Drew with contributions by Gert Franz (Railo Technologies), Andrea Campolonghi and Paul Klinkenberg (Railo Volunteers) is a comprehensive guide to getting stared with Railo Server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">To quote the back cover:</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote style=\"padding: 0px 4em; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); border-left-width: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; quotes: none; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">Railo Server is one of the quickest ways to start developing complex web applications online. Widely considered as the fastest CFML (ColdFusion Markup Language) engine, Railo allows you to create dynamic web pages that can change depending on user input, database lookups, or even the time of day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">Railo 3 Beginner&#39;s Guide will show you how to get up and running with Railo, as well as developing your web applications with the greatest of ease. You will learn how to install Railo and the basics of CFML to allow you to gradually build up your knowledge, and your dynamic web applications, as the book progresses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">Using Packt&#39;s Beginner&#39;s Guide approach, this book will guide you, with step-by-step instructions, through installing the Railo Server on various environments. You will learn how to use caches, resources, Event Gateways and special scripting functions that will allow you to create webpages with limitless functionality. You will even explore methods of extending Railo by adding your own tags to the server and building custom extensions. Railo 3 Beginner,s Guide is a must for anyone getting to grips with Railo Server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">What you will learn from this book :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em 40px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style: square; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Step-by-step instructions for developing web sites with CFML</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Learn about all the resource types available and how to handle them</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Easy to follow steps to optimise your application for high traffic</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Create dynamic applications with the in-built Hibernate ORM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Secure your server by setting up access restrictions and passwords</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Convert and display multimedia within your webpages</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\">Create your own extensions for custom functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(120, 122, 125); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;\">You can buy the eBook with all the currently published chapters as well as the full paper version when it&#39;s released directly from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.packtpub.com/railo-3-beginners-guide-to-develop-deploy-complex-applications-online/book\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(255, 135, 6); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\" title=\"Railo 3 Beginner‚Äôs Guide: RAW Book &amp; eBook | Packt Publishing Technical &amp; IT Book and eBook Store\">PacktPub Directly</a></p>\r\n',0,'2014-08-11 10:15:31','2014-08-11 10:15:31',NULL,1,NULL,'Railo for Beginners, written by Mark Drew with contributions by Gert Franz (Railo Technologies), Andrea Campolonghi and Paul Klinkenberg (Railo Volunteers) is a comprehensive guide to getting stared with Railo Server. ...'),(11,'Railo Server software archive now online','<p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; border: 0px; o